  "text": "Next we consider a generalized procedure to form the independent set complex of an arbitrary simplicial complex as in [CITATION_1] . This construction again yields a shifted complex if and only if we start with a shifted complex. Finally, we end with a result which shows that the dominance complex of a graph equals the neighborhood complex if and only if the graph is threshold.",
